You'll need to install: 
setuptools (run the ez-setup file)
numpy (sudo apt-get install python-numpy python-scipy)
matplotlib (sudo apt-get install python-matplotlib)

Then download networkx's *.egg file from here (http://pypi.python.org/pypi/networkx/) and install it by calling easy_install from the command-line shell, e.g.:

$ easy_install networkx-1.7rc1-py2.7.egg

Linux Ubuntu and Debian

From the terminal run the following command:

$ sudo apt-get install python-networkx
